\begin_layout Subsection
Labels and cross-references
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Labels can be used to refer to mathematical formulas 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:surface of a sphere"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:volume of a sphere"

\end_inset

, to table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Numbers"

\end_inset

 and figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:The-geoid"

\end_inset

.
 To create a label use the menu Insert / Label.
 Then to refer to a label go to the menu Insert / Cross-reference.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Citations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
References can be managed in a Bibtex file with a software such as Jabref.
 Go to Insert / List/TOC / Bibtex Bibliography / Add / Browse / Add.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once a bibliography has been added to the document, you can cite documents
 inside with a call to Insert / Citation.
 For example 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Peng2011"

\end_inset

 provided a nice list of recommendations for reproducible research.
\end_layout

