\begin_layout Subsection
Shortcuts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Well known shortcturs are already available in Lyx.
 For example use CTRL+C to copy selected text and CTRL+V to paste selected
 text.
 To copy atable from a spreadsheet inside a Lyx table, use CTRL+SHIFT+V,
 this preserve some elements of formatting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Menu actions can be mapped to create new keyboard shortcuts.
 This can be very usefull for actions used frequently.
 For example citation insert can be mapped to the CTRL+SHIFT+C shortcut
 (or another key combination if your prefer).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Document export
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lyx is mostly used to generate articles and reports in PDF format.
 Lyx documents can also be exported to html or rich text format (compatible
 with microsoft word).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is important to note that Lyx documents can be exported to Latex.
 The underlying Latex can be displayed at all times from the View/Source
 pane menu.
\end_layout

